16M1

Modify the cylinder height model, m16.1, so that the exponent 3 on height is instead a free parameter. Do you recover the value of 3 or not? Plot the posterior predictions for the new model. How do they differ from those of m16.1?

Data and original model

data(Howell1)
d <- Howell1

# scale observed variables
d$w <- d$weight / mean(d$weight)
d$h <- d$height / mean(d$height)

## R code 16.2
m16.1 <- ulam(
    alist(
        w ~ dlnorm( mu , sigma ),
        exp(mu) <- 3.141593 * k * p^2 * h^3,
        p ~ beta( 2 , 18 ),
        k ~ exponential( 0.5 ),
        sigma ~ exponential( 1 )
    ), data=d , chains=4 , cores=4 )

stancode(m16m1)
data{
    int male[544];
    vector[544] age;
    vector[544] weight;
    vector[544] height;
    vector[544] w;
    vector[544] h;
}
parameters{
    real<lower=0> a;
    real<lower=0,upper=1> p;
    real<lower=0> k;
    real<lower=0> sigma;
}
model{
    vector[544] mu;
    sigma ~ exponential( 1 );
    k ~ exponential( 0.5 );
    p ~ beta( 2 , 18 );
    a ~ gamma( 7/0.5 , 1/0.5 );
    for ( i in 1:544 ) {
        mu[i] = 3.141593 * k * p^2 * h[i]^a;
        mu[i] = log(mu[i]);
    }
    w ~ lognormal( mu , sigma );
}
## R code 16.2
m16m1.alt <- ulam(
    alist(
        w ~ dlnorm( mu , sigma ),
        exp(mu) <- 3.141593 * k * p^2 * h^a,
        a ~ exponential(0.3),
        p ~ beta( 2 , 18 ),
        k ~ exponential( 0.5 ),
        sigma ~ exponential( 1 )
    ), data=d , chains=4 , cores=4 )

## R code 16.3
h_seq <- seq( from=0 , to=max(d$h) , length.out=30 )
w_sim <- sim( m16.1 , data=list(h=h_seq) )
mu_mean <- apply( w_sim , 2 , mean )
w_CI <- apply( w_sim , 2 , PI )
plot( d$h , d$w , xlim=c(0,max(d$h)) , ylim=c(0,max(d$w)) , col=rangi2 ,
      lwd=2 , xlab="height (scaled)" , ylab="weight (scaled)" )
lines( h_seq , mu_mean )
shade( w_CI , h_seq )

## plus estimate from new model
w_sim2 <- sim( m16m1.alt , data=list(h=h_seq) )
mu_mean2 <- apply( w_sim2 , 2 , mean )
w_CI2 <- apply( w_sim2 , 2 , PI )
lines( h_seq , mu_mean2, lty=2 )
shade( w_CI2 , h_seq, col=col.alpha("yellow",
                                    0.25) )

## R code 16.14
sim_lynx_hare <- function( n_steps , init , theta , dt=0.002 ) {
    L <- rep(NA,n_steps)
    H <- rep(NA,n_steps)
    L[1] <- init[1]
    H[1] <- init[2]
    for ( i in 2:n_steps ) {
        H[i] <- H[i-1] + dt*H[i-1]*( theta[1] - theta[2]*L[i-1] )
        L[i] <- L[i-1] + dt*L[i-1]*( theta[3]*H[i-1] - theta[4] )
    }
    return( cbind(L,H) )
}

## R code 16.15
